<h3 id="what-went-wrong-">What went wrong ?</h3>

<p>AWS Lamba obtains IAM role credentials as environment variables. These are not supposed to be accessible but someimes developers tend to dump these during errors to help with debugging. Thatâ€™s why when I used alphabets instead of digits the website behaved pretty well and showed me a alert dialog but the url it was sending request to showed the error message and those environment variables were exposed.</p>

